b cultures, Limbrick rethinks the relation of Arab cinema to modernism and further engages debates about the use of modernist forms by filmmakers in the Global South. This original study offers new routes for thinking about world cinema and modernism in the Middle East and North Africa, and about Arab cinema in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszMorocco. 0aMotion pictureszArab countries. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aarab cinema.  aarab culture.  aarab films.  aarab renaissance.  acultural production.  afilm studies.  afilm theory.  afilmmaker.  afreedom.  agender.  aglobal south.  aintertextuality.  aislam.  amaghrib.  amiddle east.  amodernism.  amorocco.  amoumen smihi.  anahda.  anew arab cinema.  anonfiction.  anorth africa.  apostcolonialism.  areligion.  asecularism.  asexuality.  asoundscapes.  atangier.  atransnational.  aworld cinema.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974333zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974333423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974333.jpg  a978-3-11